#ident	"@(#)oamintf:devices/erase/Help	1.3.2.1"
ABSTRACT:
	The "erase" task erases a removable volume.  Its main purpose is
	to remove data so that it is no longer readable by anyone.
	Once performed, it is irreversible.  A volume cannot be erased if
	it is currently mounted or otherwise busy.

Menu.erase:Devices Available
	The devices available menu contains an entry for each type
	of device which supports the erase operation.
	Select the desired device type from the menu.  You will then
	be prompted for a device group and/or a specific device.

devgrp:Device Group
	Enter the device group you will be working with.
	Press CHOICES to see the available device groups.

devdr:Device Drive
	Enter the device drive that will hold the volume to be erased.
	Press CHOICES to see available choices for this prompt.

Text.diskette:ABSTRACT
	At this time, insert the volume you wish to erase into the drive
	you indicated in the previous frame.  After you press CONT, the
	task will erase the volume.

Text.erase2:ABSTRACT
	The volume has been erased.  This completes the "erase" task.  If
	you would like to erase another volume, insert it into the drive
	and press CONT.

Text.eraserr:ABSTRACT
	An error occurred while attempting to erase the volume.  Make sure
	the volume is inserted into the drive properly.  To try again, press
	CONT.  To leave the "erase" task, press CANCEL.
